@startuml Diagrama de Secuencia - Crear Owner con Patrones

title Crear Owner - Flujo con Patrones de Diseño

actor "Usuario" as User
participant "OwnerController\n(MVC)" as Controller
participant "OwnerService\n(Service Layer)" as Service
participant "OwnerFactory\n(Factory Pattern)" as Factory
participant "OwnerRepository" as Repo
participant "Owner\n(Entity)" as Entity
database "Database" as DB

User -> Controller: POST /owners/new\n(formData)

activate Controller
note right of Controller
  **Responsabilidad del Controller:**
  - Validar entrada HTTP
  - Delegar a Service Layer
  - Manejar vista/redirect
  
  **NO hace:**
  - Lógica de negocio
  - Acceso directo a BD
end note

Controller -> Service: createOwner(owner)

activate Service
note right of Service
  **PATRÓN: Service Layer**
  
  **Responsabilidades:**
  - Validar reglas de negocio
  - Coordinar operaciones
  - Gestionar transacción
  - Aplicar lógica de negocio
end note

Service -> Service: validateOwner(owner)
activate Service
note right
  **Validaciones de negocio:**
  - Campos requeridos
  - Formato de teléfono
  - Reglas de dominio
end note
deactivate Service

alt Validación fallida
    Service --> Controller: throw IllegalArgumentException
    Controller --> User: Mostrar error
else Validación exitosa
    Service -> Repo: save(owner)
    activate Repo
    
    Repo -> DB: INSERT INTO owners...
    activate DB
    DB --> Repo: owner guardado
    deactivate DB
    
    Repo --> Service: owner (con ID)
    deactivate Repo
    
    Service --> Controller: owner creado
    deactivate Service
    
    Controller -> Controller: redirectAttributes\n.addFlashAttribute("message")
    
    Controller --> User: redirect:/owners/{id}
    deactivate Controller
end

== Alternativa con Factory Pattern ==

User -> Controller: Crear owner con\ndatos predeterminados

activate Controller
Controller -> Factory: createDefaultOwner()

activate Factory
note right of Factory
  **PATRÓN: Factory**
  
  **Ventajas:**
  - Creación consistente
  - Valores predeterminados
  - Útil para testing
end note

Factory -> Entity: new Owner()
activate Entity
Entity --> Factory: owner
deactivate Entity

Factory -> Factory: setFirstName("John")\nsetLastName("Doe")\nsetAddress(...)\n...

Factory --> Controller: owner configurado
deactivate Factory

Controller -> Service: createOwner(owner)
Service -> Repo: save(owner)
Repo --> Service: owner guardado
Service --> Controller: owner creado
Controller --> User: redirect:/owners/{id}
deactivate Controller

== Alternativa con Builder Pattern ==

User -> Controller: Crear owner con\nBuilder Pattern

activate Controller
Controller -> Factory: builder()

activate Factory
Factory --> Controller: OwnerBuilder
deactivate Factory

Controller -> Controller: builder\n  .withFirstName("John")\n  .withLastName("Doe")\n  .withAddress("123 Main")\n  .withCity("NYC")\n  .withTelephone("1234567890")\n  .build()

note right of Controller
  **PATRÓN: Builder**
  
  **Ventajas:**
  - API fluida y legible
  - Validación en build()
  - Campos opcionales
  - Inmutabilidad posible
end note

Controller -> Service: createOwner(owner)
Service -> Repo: save(owner)
Repo --> Service: owner guardado
Service --> Controller: owner creado
Controller --> User: redirect:/owners/{id}
deactivate Controller

@enduml
